The paper discusses the language recognition power of quantum finite automata, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also explores the structural properties of the automata, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of quantum mechanics in the automata suggests cs.QL (Quantum Physics) as another possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the recognition power of the automata, which could be related to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
